Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
init_oa_foundry_rule(25.10)                        init_oa_foundry_rule(25.10)

Name
       init_oa_foundry_rule

Syntax
       init_oa_foundry_rule <foundry_rule_name>

       Type: String

       Default: NULL

       Specifies  the  foundry  constraint  group to be used in OpenAccess. If
       your technology library contains multiple  foundry_innovus_<XXXX>  con-
       straint  groups, use the init_oa_foundry_rule variable to specify which
       one of them has to be read in during design initialization. This  vari-
       able is used by the init_design command.

Example
              * The  following  command  specifies  foundry_innovus_2  as  the
                foundry constraint group to be used during design  initializa-
                tion:

                set init_oa_foundry_rule {foundry_innovus_2}

Related Information
              * init_design

